<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-30T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="831" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/142: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-30T17:00:00+00:00">January 30, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received January 30—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>41. Embassy’s telegram 27,<note n="37" xml:id="d831fn37">January 21,
                                    6 p.m., <ref target="#pg_1005">p. 1005</ref>.</note> Foreign
                                Office informs the Embassy as follows: <list>
                                    <label>(1)</label>
                                    <item>Notes regarding French Zone of Morocco and Tangier Zone
                                        were exchanged with the French yesterday in London.</item>
                                    <label>(2)</label>
                                    <item>Arrangement is not to come into effect until a date to be
                                        fixed later by mutual agreement.</item>
                                    <label>(3)</label>
                                    <item>Foreign Office states it will not consent to making the
                                        agreement on the French Zone effective except simultaneously
                                        with those on the Tangier Zone and Spanish Zone.</item>
                                    <label>(4)</label>
                                    <item>Agreement on the Tangier Zone must be approved by the
                                        Tangier Legislative Assembly and the Tangier Committee of
                                        Control under the Statute of 1923.<note n="38" xml:id="d831fn38">Convention Regarding the Organization
                                            of the Statute of the Tangier Zone, signed at Paris by
                                            France, Great Britain, and Spain, December 18, 1923,
                                            League of Nations Treaty Series, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">xxviii</hi>, p. 541; for
                                            correspondence concerning invitation to the United
                                            States to adhere to the convention, see <ref target="frus1924v02#pg_456">
                                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol.
                                                  <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 456</ref>, and
                                                <ref target="frus1925v02#pg_590">
                                                <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1925, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 590</ref>.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <label>(5)</label>
                                    <item>The agreement on the Spanish Zone has not yet been
                                        reached.</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>